  <!-- FAQs (details) -->
  <section class="section" role="region" aria-label="Health FAQ">
    <div class="inner">
      <h2 style="color:var(--pm-red);margin:0 0 10px">Health &amp; Nutrition FAQ</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>How should I thaw a 3–5 lb roast safely?</summary>
        <p class="muted">Refrigerator thaw: allow ~24 hours per 4–5 lbs. Keep on a tray to catch drips. For faster thaw, use sealed-bag cold water, changing water every 30 minutes; cook immediately after thawing.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What’s the best way to reheat leftovers?</summary>
        <p class="muted">Reheat to 165°F. Add a splash of broth or water and cover to reduce dryness; rest a few minutes before serving.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Do you have low-sodium or no-sugar options?</summary>
        <p class="muted">Yes—choose simple fresh cuts. Ask at the counter for current sausage batches with lighter seasoning.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

